{y:i} where the bluebird sings

03:05.177 --> 03:08.878
{y:i} In the big rock candy mountains

03:08.878 --> 03:11.179
{y:i} In the big rock candy mountains

03:11.379 --> 03:13.679
{y:i} All the cops have wooden legs

03:13.879 --> 03:16.280
{y:i} And the bulldogs
{y:i} all have rubber teeth

03:16.480 --> 03:18.781
{y:i} And the hens lay soft-boiled eggs

03:18.881 --> 03:21.181
{y:i} The farmers' trees
{y:i} are full of fruit

03:21.281 --> 03:23.582
{y:i} And the barns are full of hay

03:23.682 --> 03:25.882
{y:i} Oh, I'm bound to go
{y:i} where there ain't no snow

03:26.082 --> 03:28.283
{y:i} Where the rain don't fall,
{y:i} the wind don't blow

03:28.383 --> 03:31.984
{y:i} In the big rock candy mountains

03:31.984 --> 03:34.384
{y:i} In the big rock candy mountains

03:34.484 --> 03:36.585
{y:i} You never change your socks

03:36.685 --> 03:38.985
{y:i} And the little streams of alcohol

03:39.185 --> 03:41.386
{y:i} Come a-trickling down the rocks

03:41.486 --> 03:43.786
{y:i} The brakemen have to tip their hats

03:43.886 --> 03:46.087
{y:i} And the railroad bulls are blind

03:46.187 --> 03:48.587
{y:i} There's a lake of stew
{y:i} and of whiskey, too

03:48.687 --> 03:50.888
{y:i} You can paddle all around 'em
{y:i} in a big canoe

03:51.088 --> 03:54.889
{y:i} In the big rock
{y:i} candy mountains...

03:57.089 --> 03:59.090
{y:i} The jails are made of tin

03:59.290 --> 04:01.290
{y:i} And you can walk right out again

04:01.490 --> 04:03.891
{y:i} As soon as you are in

04:03.991 --> 04:06.091
{y:i} There ain't no
{y:i} short-handle shovels

04:06.191 --> 04:08.392
{y:i} No axes, saws or picks

04:08.492 --> 04:10.992
{y:i} I'm a-goin' to stay
{y:i} where you sleep all day

04:11.092 --> 04:12.993
{y:i} Where they hung the jerk
{y:i} that invented work

04:13.193 --> 04:17.194
{y:i} In the big rock candy mountains

04:22.595 --> 04:24.696
{y:i} I'll see you all this comin' fall

04:24.896 --> 04:28.896
{y:i} In the big rock candy mountains

05:03.104 --> 05:04.405
Say,

05:04.605 --> 05:08.205
any of you boys smithies?

05:09.106 --> 05:10.706
Or if not smithies per se

05:10.706 --> 05:13.507
were you otherwise trained
in the metallurgic arts

05:12.706 --> 05:17.608
before straitened circumstances forced
you into a life of aimless wanderin'?

05:26.109 --> 05:29.110
Jesus! Can't I count on you people?

05:29.210 --> 05:30.911
Sorry, Everett.

05:31.111 --> 05:35.812
Well, all right.
...we take off through that bayou...

05:35.912 --> 05:37.212
Wait a minute!

05:37.412 --> 05:40.013
Who elected you leader of this outfit?

05:40.013 --> 05:43.913
Pete, I figured it should be the one
with the capacity for abstract thought,

05:44.114 --> 05:47.114
but if that ain't the consensus'
view, then hell, let's put it to a vote.

05:47.214 --> 05:49.715
Suits me! I'm votin' for yours truly.

05:49.815 --> 05:53.716
Well, I'm votin' for yours truly, too.

05:56.816 --> 06:00.217
OK, I'm with you fellas.

06:23.222 --> 06:26.123
Mind if we join you, old-timer?

06:26.223 --> 06:31.424
Join me, m'son. Join me.

06:32.324 --> 06:35.525
You work for the railroad, Grandpa?

06:35.725 --> 06:37.926
I work for no man.

06:38.126 --> 06:42.127
- You got a name, do you?
- I have no name.

06:42.227 --> 06:46.328
That right there may be the reason
you had difficulty finding employment.

06:46.428 --> 06:49.328
Y'see, in the mart of competitive commerce...

06:49.528 --> 06:51.329
You seek a great fortune,

06:51.429 --> 06:53.929
you three who are now in chains.

06:54.129 --> 06:56.830
You will find a fortune,

06:56.930 --> 07:00.231
though it will not be
the fortune you seek.

07:00.331 --> 07:02.431
But first...

07:02.631 --> 07:08.433
first you must travel a
long and difficult road,

07:08.533 --> 07:13.234
a road fraught with peril, mm-hmm.

07:13.334 --> 07:16.334
You shall see things...

07:16.434 --> 07:18.535
wonderful to tell.

07:18.735 --> 07:22.136
You shall see a... a cow...

07:22.336 --> 07:26.837
on the roof of a cotton house, ha.

07:26.937 --> 07:31.238
And, oh, so many startling sights.

07:31.238 --> 07:34.339
I cannot tell you how
long this road shall be,

07:34.539 --> 07:37.739
but fear not the obstacles in your path,

07:37.739 --> 07:39.140
for fate has...

07:39.340 --> 07:42.440
vouchsafed your reward.

07:42.540 --> 07:45.341
Though the road may wind,

07:45.541 --> 07:48.042
and yea, your hearts grow weary,

07:48.142 --> 07:50.942
still shall ye follow them,

07:51.042 --> 07:55.943
even unto your salvation.

08:07.046 --> 08:10.947
No, the treasure's still
there, boys, believe me.

08:10.947 --> 08:13.247
But how did he know about the treasure?

08:13.447 --> 08:17.348
I don't know, Delmar. The blind
are reputed to have sensitivities
reputedly possess sensitivities

08:17.448 --> 08:19.249
compensating for their lack of sight,

08:19.449 --> 08:22.149
even to the point of developing
paranormal psychic powers.

08:22.249 --> 08:25.750
Clearly, seeing into the future
would fall neatly into that category.

08:25.950 --> 08:29.951
It's not so surprising then that an
organism deprived of its earthly vision...

08:29.951 --> 08:32.952
He said we wouldn't get it. We
wouldn't get the treasure we seek,

08:33.052 --> 08:34.751
on account of our obstacles.

08:34.852 --> 08:37.653
What the hell does he know?
He's an ignorant old man.

08:37.753 --> 08:40.554
Jesus, Pete. I told you I'd buried it myself.

08:40.654 --> 08:42.654
If your cousin still has
this here horse farm

08:42.854 --> 08:46.155
a forge and some shoeing impedimenta
to restore our liberty of movement...

08:47.555 --> 08:49.256
Hold it right there!

08:49.356 --> 08:53.156
You men from the bank?

08:53.156 --> 08:54.657
You Wash's boy?

08:54.857 --> 08:58.558
Yes, sir. And Daddy told me
I'm to shoot whoever's from the bank!

08:58.658 --> 09:01.158
Well, we ain't from the bank, young fella.

09:01.258 --> 09:04.759
Yes, sir. I'm supposed to shoot folks
servin' papers!

09:04.759 --> 09:08.360
- We ain't got no papers, neither.
- I nicked the census man.

09:08.560 --> 09:10.760
Now, there's a good boy.

09:10.860 --> 09:12.961
Is... is your daddy about?

09:24.864 --> 09:26.564
Hello, Pete.

09:26.764 --> 09:28.764
Who are your friends?

09:28.965 --> 09:31.765
Pleased to make your
acquaintance, Mr. Hogwallop.

09:31.965 --> 09:37.066
- My name's Ulysses Everett McGill...
- And I'm Delmar O'Donnel.

09:36.866 --> 09:38.667
How you been, Wash?

09:38.967 --> 09:41.867
Been what, 12, 13 years?

09:44.468 --> 09:46.568
Yeah...

09:46.769 --> 09:50.369
I expect you want them chains knocked off.

09:50.469 --> 09:53.270
They foreclosed on Cousin Vester.

09:53.270 --> 09:56.171
He hanged hisself a year come May.

09:56.271 --> 09:58.071
And Uncle Ratliff?

09:58.271 --> 10:00.472
The anthrax took most of his cows.

10:00.672 --> 10:02.272
The rest don't milk.

10:02.572 --> 10:05.373
He lost a boy to mumps.

10:05.373 --> 10:09.174
Where's Cora, Cousin Wash?

10:11.674 --> 10:15.675
Couldn't say.

10:15.575 --> 10:21.877
Mrs. Hogwallop up and R-U-N-N-O-F-T.

10:21.776 --> 10:24.877
She must have been lookin' for answers.

10:25.077 --> 10:28.278
Possibly. Good riddance,
as far as I'm concerned.

10:28.378 --> 10:31.279
I do miss her cooking, though.

10:31.379 --> 10:35.280
- This stew's awful good.
- You think so?

10:35.380 --> 10:38.080
I slaughtered this horse last Tuesday.

10:38.080 --> 10:42.681
I'm afraid she's startin' to turn.

10:45.882 --> 10:48.683
{y:i} You are my sunshine

10:48.783 --> 10:51.683
{y:i} My only sunshine

10:51.783 --> 10:53.484
{y:i} You make me happy

10:53.784 --> 10:56.084
{y:i} When skies are grey

10:56.284 --> 10:58.785
{y:i} You'll never know, dear

10:58.785 --> 11:01.385
{y:i} How much I love you

11:01.485 --> 11:06.287
{y:i} Please don't take
{y:i} my sunshine away

11:06.287 --> 11:11.388
Well, that winds up tonight's: Pass The
Biscuits, Pappy O'Daniel Flour Hour.

11:11.388 --> 11:12.788
This is Pappy O'Daniel,

11:12.888 --> 11:15.789
hopin' you folks have been
enjoyin' that old-timey music.

11:15.889 --> 11:17.789
And remember:

11:17.989 --> 11:21.490
When you're fryin' up some flapjacks,
or baking a mess of biscuits,

11:21.590 --> 11:23.390
use cool, clear water,

11:23.490 --> 11:27.691
and good, pure, Pappy O'Daniel flour.

11:27.791 --> 11:32.993
Well, guess I'll be turnin' in.
Say, uh, Cousin Wash,

11:32.993 --> 11:35.193
I suppose it'd be the acme of foolishness

11:35.393 --> 11:37.194
to enquire if you had a hairnet?

11:37.394 --> 11:40.094
I got a bunch in yond bureau.

11:40.194 --> 11:42.695
Mrs. Hogwallop's, as a matter of fact.

11:42.795 --> 11:47.296
Help yourself. I won't be needing them.

11:47.396 --> 11:48.996
{y:i} You are my sunshine

11:49.096 --> 11:52.497
{y:i} My only sunshine

11:52.597 --> 11:54.998
{y:i} You make me happy

11:55.098 --> 11:56.598
{y:i} When skies are grey...

11:58.698 --> 11:59.899
- All right, boys!

12:00.199 --> 12:01.999
How's my hair?

12:02.099 --> 12:06.500
It's the authorities!
We got you surrounded.

12:06.600 --> 12:08.501
Damn, we're in a tight spot.

12:08.701 --> 12:11.601
Just come on out and grab at air!

12:11.701 --> 12:14.202
And don't try nothin' fancy.

12:14.302 --> 12:16.803
Your situation is pretty nigh hopeless.

12:16.903 --> 12:20.603
- Damn! We're in a tight spot!
- What in the Sam Hill...?

12:20.803 --> 12:22.504
Pete's cousin turned us in for the bounty.

12:22.704 --> 12:23.804
What the hell you sayin'?!

12:24.004 --> 12:25.705
Wash is kin!

12:25.905 --> 12:27.005
Sorry, Pete!

12:27.305 --> 12:30.906
I know we're kin,
but they got this depression on.

12:30.906 --> 12:32.606
I got to do for me and mine.

12:32.806 --> 12:37.107
I'm gonna kill you!
Judas Iscariot Hogwallop!

12:37.207 --> 12:41.508
You miserable, horse-eatin' son of a bitch!

12:41.508 --> 12:43.209
Damn! We're in a tight spot.

12:43.409 --> 12:45.009
Damn his eyes!

12:45.109 --> 12:48.910
Pa always said, "Never trust a Hogwallop".

12:49.010 --> 12:51.510
Come and get us, coppers!

12:53.011 --> 12:56.512
You boys ain't leavin' us no
choice but to smoke you out.

12:56.612 --> 12:58.312
Damn! We're in a tight spot.

12:58.412 --> 12:59.412
Light her up!

12:59.712 --> 13:03.013
Hold on, boys!
Ain't you ever heard of negotiating?

13:03.113 --> 13:05.514
Maybe we can talk this thing out.
I hate fire.

13:05.514 --> 13:08.314
You lousy, low-down,
yellow-bellied skunks!

13:08.314 --> 13:10.315
Pete, we gotta speak
with one voice here.

13:10.415 --> 13:13.916
Careful with that fire, boys!

13:14.516 --> 13:16.416
Light the loft, son.

13:16.516 --> 13:18.817
Aah! I hate fire!

13:18.917 --> 13:23.118
Gapped-toothed, carpetbaggin',
motherless spawn of hell!

13:23.218 --> 13:25.918
Step back. Damn it. Look out.

13:26.118 --> 13:27.819
Holy Saint Christopher!

13:27.919 --> 13:30.419
Get away from that vehicle, champ.
She's lickin' fire.

13:31.920 --> 13:36.021
Take cover, boys! That ain't popcorn!

13:45.323 --> 13:48.223
Scatter, boys!

13:49.224 --> 13:52.124
God damn it!

13:54.925 --> 13:56.225
Get in, boys!

13:56.425 --> 13:58.826
I'm gonna R-U-N-N-O-F-T!

13:58.926 --> 14:02.727
Come on, boys! Come on! Come on!

14:02.827 --> 14:06.928
What are you doing here? You ought
to be in bed, clump snatcher.

14:07.028 --> 14:10.028
You ain't the boss of me!

14:16.030 --> 14:19.730
You candy-butted, car-thievin' so-and-sos!

14:19.930 --> 14:21.931
I curse your names!

14:22.131 --> 14:24.832
Go back home and mind your pa!

14:28.332 --> 14:31.833
What's the damn problem?

14:32.433 --> 14:35.934
I can get the part from Bristol.
It'll take two weeks. Here's your pomade.

14:36.034 --> 14:38.835
Two weeks?
That don't do me no good.

14:39.035 --> 14:41.535
Nearest Ford auto man's in Bristol.

14:41.535 --> 14:44.836
Hold on. I don't want this pomade,
I want Dapper Dan.

14:45.036 --> 14:47.937
I don't carry Dapper Dan.
I carry Fop.

14:48.037 --> 14:51.438
Well, I don't want Fop. Goddamn it!
I'm a Dapper Dan man!

14:51.538 --> 14:54.138
Watch your language, young fellow,
this is a public market.

14:54.338 --> 14:58.639
Now, if you want Dapper Dan, I can order
it so you'll have it in a couple of weeks.

14:58.739 --> 15:02.240
Ain't this a geographical oddity!
Two weeks from everywhere.

15:02.440 --> 15:04.341
Forget it.

15:04.441 --> 15:08.241
Just a dozen hairnets.

15:08.241 --> 15:10.942
Well, didn't look like a one-horse town,

15:11.042 --> 15:13.443
but try finding a decent hair jelly.

15:13.543 --> 15:17.744
- Gopher, Everett?
- And no transmission belt for two weeks.

15:17.744 --> 15:20.444
Huh? They dam that river on the 21st.

15:20.544 --> 15:22.945
- Today is the 17th.
- Don't I know it.

15:23.145 --> 15:25.745
We got but four days to get to that treasure.

15:25.845 --> 15:28.646
After that, it'll be at the bottom of a lake.

15:28.746 --> 15:30.647
We ain't gonna make it walkin'.

15:30.847 --> 15:32.847
- That's right...
- Gopher, Everett?

15:33.047 --> 15:35.348
But the old tactician's got a plan.

15:35.448 --> 15:39.348
For the transportation, that is. I don't
know how I'll keep my coiffure in order.

15:39.449 --> 15:42.549
How's this a plan?
How we gonna get a car?

15:42.549 --> 15:47.050
Sell that. I figure you can only have
painful association for Wash.

15:47.150 --> 15:51.651
"To Washington Bartholomew Hogwallop,

15:51.751 --> 15:53.152
from his lovin' Cora."

15:53.352 --> 15:58.753
- "Amor fidel... lis."
- It was in his bureau,

15:58.753 --> 16:02.054
I reckon it'll fetch us enough
cash for a good auto voiture

16:02.054 --> 16:03.854
and a little leftover besides.

16:04.054 --> 16:06.455
Whoo! You got light fingers, Everett.

16:06.655 --> 16:10.356
- Gopher?
- You miserable little snake.

16:10.456 --> 16:12.256
You stole from my kin!

16:12.356 --> 16:14.957
Who was fixin' to betray us.

16:15.057 --> 16:17.057
You didn't know that at the time.

16:17.257 --> 16:19.258
So I borrowed it till I did know.

16:19.358 --> 16:21.358
That don't make no sense!

16:21.458 --> 16:24.359
It's a fool who looks for logic
in the chambers of the human heart.

16:24.459 --> 16:28.960
Now... What the hell is that singing?

16:30.160 --> 16:35.761
Appears to be some kind
of a... congregation.

16:35.861 --> 16:39.462
Care for some gopher?

16:41.062 --> 16:42.863
No, thank you, Delmar.

16:42.963 --> 16:45.964
A third of a gopher'd
only arouse my appetite

16:46.064 --> 16:48.364
without beddin' her back down.

16:48.464 --> 16:50.765
Oh, you can have the whole thing.

16:50.865 --> 16:53.765
Me and Pete already had one.

16:53.965 --> 17:02.767
We ran across a whole...
gopher... village.

17:05.167 --> 17:08.669
{y:i} O brothers, let's go down

17:08.769 --> 17:12.470
{y:i} Let's go down, come on down

17:12.569 --> 17:15.970
{y:i} Come on, brothers, let's go down

17:16.069 --> 17:20.271
{y:i} Down in the river to pray

17:20.271 --> 17:24.071
{y:i} As I went down
{y:i} in the river to pray

17:24.071 --> 17:26.973
{y:i} Studyin' about that good old way

17:27.173 --> 17:30.574
{y:i} And who shall wear
{y:i} the starry crown

17:30.574 --> 17:34.975
{y:i} Good Lord, show me the way

17:35.075 --> 17:38.676
{y:i} O fathers, let's go down

17:38.676 --> 17:42.176
{y:i} Let's go down, come on down

17:42.276 --> 17:45.577
{y:i} O fathers, let's go down

17:45.777 --> 17:49.978
{y:i} Down in the river to pray

17:50.078 --> 17:53.979
{y:i} As I went down
{y:i} in the river to pray

17:53.979 --> 17:57.080
{y:i} Studying about that good old way

17:57.280 --> 18:00.581
{y:i} And who shall wear
{y:i} the robe and crown

18:00.681 --> 18:05.382
{y:i} Good lord, show me the way

18:05.382 --> 18:08.782
{y:i} O mothers, let's go down

18:08.782 --> 18:12.083
{y:i} Come on down,
{y:i} don't you wanna go down?

18:12.283 --> 18:15.984
{y:i} Come on, mothers,
{y:i} let's go down...

18:15.984 --> 18:19.085
Well, I guess hard times flush the chumps.

18:19.285 --> 18:21.385
Everybody's lookin' for answers.

18:24.986 --> 18:26.686
Where the hell's he going?

18:26.886 --> 18:30.787
The Father, the Son and the Holy Ghost.

18:30.887 --> 18:34.788
{y:i} Good Lord, show me the way

18:34.888 --> 18:39.289
{y:i} O sinners, let's go down...

18:39.389 --> 18:41.690
Well, I'll be a son of a bitch.

18:41.890 --> 18:43.790
Delmar's been saved.

18:43.990 --> 18:46.891
Well, that's it, boys. I been redeemed.

18:47.091 --> 18:51.292
The preacher done washed away
all my sins and transgressions.

18:51.292 --> 18:54.193
It's the straight and narrow
from here on out.

18:54.293 --> 18:56.793
And heaven everlasting's my reward.

18:56.993 --> 19:00.194
Delmar, what are you on about?
We got bigger fish to fry.

19:00.194 --> 19:03.195
The preacher said
all my sins is washed away,

19:03.395 --> 19:06.395
including that Piggly Wiggly
I knocked over in Yazoo.

19:06.495 --> 19:08.496
I thought you said you were
innocent of those charges?

19:08.696 --> 19:10.896
Well, I was lying.

19:11.096 --> 19:14.797
And the preacher said that
that sin's been washed away, too.

19:14.897 --> 19:18.198
Neither God nor man's
got nothin' on me now.

19:18.298 --> 19:23.199
Come on in, boys. The water is fine.

19:28.700 --> 19:31.501
Come on, boy. There, boy. Good doggy.

19:33.902 --> 19:37.703
All right, boys, we got the scent.

19:40.003 --> 19:43.704
- The preacher said it absolved us.
- For Him, not for the law.

19:43.904 --> 19:46.605
I'm surprised. I gave you credit
for more brains than Delmar.

19:46.605 --> 19:50.705
- But there were witnesses seen us redeemed.
- That's not the issue, Delmar.

19:50.805 --> 19:54.106
Even if it did put you square with the Lord, the
state of Mississippi's a little more hard-nosed.

19:54.106 --> 19:57.507
You shoulda joined us, Everett.
It couldn'a hurt none.

19:57.707 --> 20:01.108
Hell, at least it woulda washed away
the stink of that pomade.

20:01.208 --> 20:04.809
Joining you fools in a ridiculous
superstition? Thank you, anyway.

20:04.909 --> 20:10.210
And I like the smell of my hair treatment,
the pleasin' odour's half the point.

20:10.210 --> 20:12.210
Baptism.

20:12.310 --> 20:14.611
You two are dumber
than a bag of hammers.

20:14.811 --> 20:16.611
Well, I guess you're just my cross to bear.

20:16.911 --> 20:21.813
Pull over, Everett. Let's give
that coloured boy a lift.

20:27.314 --> 20:29.614
You folks going past Tishomingo?

20:29.714 --> 20:32.615
Sure, hop in.

20:39.216 --> 20:41.617
How you doin', son? Name's Everett.

20:41.717 --> 20:45.118
These two soggy sons of bitches
are Pete and Delmar.

20:45.118 --> 20:48.919
Keep your fingers away from Pete's
mouth, he ain't eaten for 13 years,

20:49.119 --> 20:51.419
'cept prison food, gopher,
and a little greasy horse.

20:51.519 --> 20:55.520
Thanks for the lift, sir.
My name's Tommy. Tommy Johnson.

20:55.520 --> 20:57.421
How you doin', Tommy?

20:57.521 --> 21:00.621
Say, I haven't seen a house
out here for miles.

21:00.721 --> 21:03.222
What are you doing out
in the middle of nowhere?

21:03.422 --> 21:06.123
Well I had to be at that there
crossroads last midnight.

21:06.123 --> 21:08.023
Sell my soul to the Devil.

21:08.323 --> 21:10.824
Ain't it a small world, spiritually speakin'?

21:10.824 --> 21:15.025
Pete and Delmar have just been baptized and saved.
I guess I'm the only one that remains unaffiliated.

21:15.125 --> 21:17.325
This ain't no laughin' matter, Everett.

21:17.425 --> 21:19.226
What'd the Devil give you for your soul, Tommy?

21:19.426 --> 21:22.826
Well, he taught me to play
this here guitar real good.

21:22.826 --> 21:27.127
Oh, son, for that you traded
your everlasting soul?

21:27.227 --> 21:28.728
Well, I wasn't usin' it.

21:28.928 --> 21:33.029
I've always wondered,
what's the Devil look like?

21:33.029 --> 21:36.529
Well, of course there are all manner
of lesser imps and demons, Pete,

21:36.629 --> 21:40.330
but the great Satan himself is red
and scaly with a bifurcated tail,

21:40.430 --> 21:43.931
- and carries a hayfork.
- Oh, no. No, sir.

21:43.931 --> 21:47.332
He's white. As white as you folks.

21:47.532 --> 21:50.333
With empty eyes and a big, hollow voice.

21:50.533 --> 21:54.233
He loves travel around with
a mean old hound, that's right.

21:54.233 --> 21:56.234
He told you to go to Tishomingo?

21:56.334 --> 21:59.235
Well, no, sir.
Why, that was my idea.

21:59.335 --> 22:01.235
I heard there's a man down there,

22:01.335 --> 22:03.736
he pays folks money to sing into his can.

22:03.836 --> 22:07.737
They say he pays extra
if'n you play real good.

22:07.737 --> 22:09.637
Tishomingo, huh?

22:09.737 --> 22:11.337
How much he pay?

22:27.041 --> 22:31.742
All right, boys, follow my lead.

22:35.443 --> 22:37.843
Hello?

22:38.043 --> 22:42.644
- Who's the honcho around here?
- I am. Who are you?

22:42.644 --> 22:47.145
Well, sir, I'm Jordan Rivers, and
these here are the Soggy Bottom Boys,

22:47.145 --> 22:49.146
out of Cottonillia, Mississippi.

22:49.246 --> 22:51.646
Songs of salvation to salve the soul.

22:51.847 --> 22:55.647
Uh, we hear that you pay good
money to sing into a can.

22:55.747 --> 22:59.048
Well, that all depends.
You boys do Negro songs?

22:59.048 --> 23:03.949
Um... Well, uh, sir, we are Negroes.

23:03.949 --> 23:07.950
All except for our accomp... accomp...
the fella that plays the guitar.

23:08.050 --> 23:10.251
Yeah, well, I don't record Negro songs.

23:10.451 --> 23:13.852
No, I'm lookin' for
some old-timey material.

23:13.752 --> 23:15.952
You see, people can't seem
to get enough of it

23:16.052 --> 23:19.553
since we started broadcasting it
on the Pappy O'Daniel Flour Hour,

23:19.653 --> 23:21.953
so thank you for stopping by...

23:22.053 --> 23:26.955
Sir, the Soggy Bottom Boys have been
steeped in old-timey material.

23:26.854 --> 23:29.555
- Heck, we're silly with it, ain't we, boys?
- That's right.

23:29.755 --> 23:31.756
That's right. We ain't really Negroes.

23:31.956 --> 23:34.056
Except for our accompanist.

23:36.457 --> 23:40.758
{y:i} I am a man

23:40.858 --> 23:43.658
{y:i} Of constant sorrow

23:43.658 --> 23:49.760
{y:i} I've seen trouble all my days

23:49.760 --> 23:54.161
{y:i} I bid farewell

23:54.161 --> 23:56.761
{y:i} To old Kentucky

23:56.861 --> 23:59.262
{y:i} The place where I

23:59.362 --> 24:02.062
{y:i} Was born and raised

24:02.062 --> 24:04.863
{y:i} The place where he

24:05.063 --> 24:08.464
{y:i} Was born and raised

24:08.564 --> 24:12.965
{y:i} For six long years

24:12.965 --> 24:15.566
{y:i} I've been in trouble

24:15.666 --> 24:18.366
{y:i} No pleasure here

24:18.466 --> 24:21.767
{y:i} On Earth I found

24:21.967 --> 24:26.168
{y:i} For in this world

24:26.168 --> 24:28.368
{y:i} I'm bound to ramble

24:28.468 --> 24:31.469
{y:i} I have no friends

24:31.669 --> 24:34.270
{y:i} To help me now

24:34.470 --> 24:36.970
{y:i} He has no friends

24:37.070 --> 24:40.671
{y:i} To help him now

24:40.671 --> 24:45.172
{y:i} Maybe your friends think

24:45.172 --> 24:47.773
{y:i} I'm just a stranger

24:47.873 --> 24:50.373
{y:i} My face you never

24:50.473 --> 24:51.774
{y:i} Will see no more

24:54.074 --> 24:58.975
{y:i} But there is one promise

24:58.975 --> 25:00.976
{y:i} That is given

25:01.176 --> 25:03.676
{y:i} I'll meet you on

25:03.876 --> 25:06.477
{y:i} God's golden shore

25:06.577 --> 25:09.278
{y:i} He'll meet you on

25:09.378 --> 25:14.379
{y:i} God's golden shore

25:15.379 --> 25:18.980
Whoo! Hot damn, son! I do believe
you did sell your soul to the Devil!

25:19.080 --> 25:20.380
Whoo-ee!

25:20.480 --> 25:24.381
Boy, that was some mighty fine
a-pickin' and a-singin'.

25:24.381 --> 25:25.681
I'll tell you what.

25:25.981 --> 25:28.182
Ahem. You come on in here, you...

25:28.382 --> 25:32.883
you sign these papers here,
I'm gonna give you $10 apiece.

25:32.883 --> 25:39.084
Uh, OK, sir, but Mert and
uh... Aloysious'll have to sign X's.

25:39.084 --> 25:43.085
- Only four of us can write.
- That'd be fine.

25:43.085 --> 25:45.586
- Ha ha!
- Whoo!

25:45.786 --> 25:49.087
Hey, mister, I don't mean to
be telling tales out of school,

25:49.187 --> 25:52.988
but there's a fella in there'll pay
you $10 if you sing into his can.

25:53.088 --> 25:56.088
I'm not here to make a record,
you dumb cracker.

25:56.288 --> 25:58.089
They broadcast me on the radio.

25:58.289 --> 26:01.189
That's Governor Menelaus,
"Pass the Biscuits, Pappy O'Daniel".

26:01.289 --> 26:05.490
And he'd appreciate it if you ate his
farina and voted him a second term.

26:05.490 --> 26:08.191
- Finest governor we ever had in Mississippi.
- In any state.

26:08.291 --> 26:10.592
Lord, yes, every parish or precinct.
He was making a bigger point.

26:10.692 --> 26:14.492
Ain't you gonna press the flesh, Pappy?
Do some politickin'?

26:14.492 --> 26:16.693
I'll press your flesh,
you dim-witted son'bitch.

26:16.893 --> 26:20.694
Don't tell your Pappy how to court the
electorate. We ain't one-at-a-timin' here.

26:20.794 --> 26:22.494
We're mass communicatin'!

26:22.594 --> 26:25.195
Oh, yes, that's a powerful new force.

26:25.395 --> 26:26.695
Shake a leg, Junior.

26:26.995 --> 26:29.396
Thank God your mammy died givin' birth.

26:29.496 --> 26:31.096
If she'd seen you she'd have died of shame.

26:31.196 --> 26:33.097
Well, hi there! How you doin'?

26:34.997 --> 26:40.598
{y:i} Hard time yearnin'
{y:i} where you go

26:40.598 --> 26:46.200
{y:i} Times is harder
{y:i} than ever been before

26:50.901 --> 26:54.001
{y:i} And the people are driftin'

26:54.101 --> 26:56.702
{y:i} From door to door

26:56.802 --> 26:58.202
{y:i} Can't find no heaven

26:58.302 --> 27:01.703
{y:i} I don't care where they go

27:01.903 --> 27:07.104
{y:i} Mm-hmm, mm-hmm

27:07.204 --> 27:11.705
{y:i} Mm-hm, mm-hmm

27:11.805 --> 27:14.306
{y:i} Say you had money

27:14.306 --> 27:16.807
{y:i} You better be sure

27:16.907 --> 27:18.807
{y:i} These hard times will drive you

27:18.907 --> 27:21.808
{y:i} From door to door

27:21.908 --> 27:24.208
{y:i} Uh-hmm

27:24.308 --> 27:27.109
{y:i} Mm-hmm

27:27.209 --> 27:33.210
{y:i} Uh-hmm, mm-hmm...

27:33.010 --> 27:35.411
Let's bed down here for the night.

27:35.511 --> 27:39.212
Yeah, it stinks in that old barn.

27:39.312 --> 27:40.712
Suits me.

27:40.912 --> 27:46.813
Pretty soon it'll be nothin' but
featherbeds and silk sheets.

27:46.913 --> 27:49.514
{y:i} Mm-hm...

27:49.514 --> 27:51.314
A million dollars.

27:51.615 --> 27:53.515
Million point two.

27:53.715 --> 27:58.416
- 500,000 each.
- 400, Delmar.

27:58.416 --> 28:05.118
Pete, what are you gonna do
with your share of the treasure?

28:05.018 --> 28:07.618
Go out west somewhere.

28:07.718 --> 28:11.319
Open a fine restaurant.

28:11.219 --> 28:14.720
I'm gonna be the maitre d'.

28:14.820 --> 28:17.520
Greet all the swells.

28:17.520 --> 28:20.821
Go to work every day in a bow tie,

28:21.021 --> 28:23.022
tuxedo.

28:23.222 --> 28:26.722
And all the staff say "yes, sir" and...

28:26.822 --> 28:28.123
"no, sir"...

28:28.323 --> 28:31.724
and "in a jiffy, Pete".

28:31.824 --> 28:35.825
And all my meals for free.

28:38.625 --> 28:40.426
What about you, Delmar,

28:40.626 --> 28:43.826
what are you gonna do with
your share of that dough?

28:43.926 --> 28:47.627
I'm gonna visit them
foreclosin' son of a guns

28:47.727 --> 28:51.328
down at the Indianola Savings and Loan.

28:51.328 --> 28:57.429
Slap that money on the barrel head
and buy back the family farm.

28:57.429 --> 29:02.030
You ain't no kind of man
if you ain't got land.

29:02.030 --> 29:03.931
What about you, Everett?

29:04.131 --> 29:07.932
What you have in mind when
you stole it in the first place?

29:07.932 --> 29:14.233
Ahem. I... didn't have no plan.

29:14.233 --> 29:17.134
Well, that hardly sounds like you.

29:17.234 --> 29:20.435
All right, boys! It's the authorities!

29:20.635 --> 29:23.235
Your situation is pretty hopeless!

29:23.235 --> 29:25.636
Damn, they found our car.

29:25.736 --> 29:28.937
We ain't got the time
and nary the inclination

29:29.037 --> 29:31.537
to chat with you boys any further.

29:31.637 --> 29:33.738
Damn, we got to skedaddle.

29:33.938 --> 29:37.839
I left my pomade in the car.
Maybe I can creep up.

29:37.939 --> 29:42.240
Don't be a fool, Everett.
We got to R-U-N-N-O-F-T.

29:42.340 --> 29:44.240
Where's Tommy?

29:44.340 --> 29:49.541
Already lit out, scared out of his wits.

29:50.541 --> 29:53.442
Let's go!

29:53.542 --> 29:55.543
Well, hell, it ain't square one.

29:55.643 --> 29:59.744
Ain't no one gonna pick up three
filthy unshaved hitchhikers.

29:59.744 --> 30:03.744
And one of them a know-it-all
who can't keep his trap shut.

30:03.844 --> 30:08.045
Pete, the personal rancour reflected in that
remark I don't intend to dignify with comment.

30:08.145 --> 30:12.346
But I would like to address your general
attitude of hopeless negativism.

30:12.446 --> 30:15.247
Consider the lilies of the goddam field.

30:15.347 --> 30:18.248
Or, hell, look at Delmar here
as your paradigm of hope.

30:18.448 --> 30:20.048
Yeah. Look at me.

30:20.148 --> 30:24.149
You may call it an unreasoning
optimism, you may call it obtuse,

30:24.149 --> 30:27.350
but the plain and simple fact
is that we got close to...

30:27.550 --> 30:30.150
three days before they...

30:34.651 --> 30:38.852
...dam that river.

30:59.857 --> 31:03.758
Is this the road to Itta Bena?

31:03.758 --> 31:06.559
Uh... Itta Bena?

31:06.659 --> 31:10.960
Itta Bena?
If you stay on this here road.

31:11.060 --> 31:14.360
That ain't right,
I was thinking of, uh...

31:14.460 --> 31:16.761
- Take this road.
- Nah, that ain't right.

31:16.961 --> 31:19.062
Seems to me there's a road...

31:19.262 --> 31:21.962
Cow road that used to lead all the way...

31:22.162 --> 31:25.463
Well, most of the way...
Er, that ain't right, either.

31:25.463 --> 31:32.365
- Hop in while you give it a think.
- Right. Delmar.

31:39.166 --> 31:41.967
Any of you boys know your
way around a Walther PPK?

31:42.067 --> 31:47.468
Well, see, that's where we can't help ya.
I don't believe it's in Mississippi.

31:47.868 --> 31:51.269
Friend, some of your folding
money has come unstowed.

31:51.269 --> 31:54.069
Just stuff it down that
sack, will you?

31:54.170 --> 31:56.270
You boys aren't bad men, I take it?

31:56.370 --> 31:58.570
Well, it's funny you should ask.

31:58.771 --> 32:02.871
I was bad till yesterday, but me
and Pete here have been saved.

32:02.871 --> 32:05.672
I'm Delmar, and that there is Everett.

32:05.872 --> 32:09.673
George Nelson. It's a pleasure.

32:09.673 --> 32:13.874
Grab the tiller, will you, buddy?

32:17.775 --> 32:19.775
Hand me that chopper.

32:19.975 --> 32:23.076
Say, what line of work you in, George?

32:23.176 --> 32:24.976
Ha ha ha ha!

32:25.077 --> 32:26.477
Come and get me, coppers!

32:26.577 --> 32:30.878
You flatfooted, lame-brained,
soft-ass sons of bitches!

32:30.878 --> 32:35.979
Ah ha ha ha ha! No one can catch me!
I'm George Nelson!

32:35.979 --> 32:40.280
I'm bigger than any John,
live or limp!

32:40.280 --> 32:45.181
I'm ten an' a half feet tall
and ain't yet fully grown!

32:46.081 --> 32:52.083
Cows. I hate cows worse than coppers!

32:52.683 --> 32:54.883
Oh, George... Not the livestock.

32:55.083 --> 33:00.385
Come on, you miserable salaried
sons of bitches! Come and get me!

33:15.288 --> 33:18.089
Come on, boys, we're going for the record.

33:18.089 --> 33:19.589
Three banks in two hours!

33:26.791 --> 33:30.091
OK, folks, hold the applause
and drop your drawers!

33:30.091 --> 33:35.793
I'm George Nelson, and I'm here
to sack the city Itta Bena!

33:35.592 --> 33:37.893
He's a live wire, though, ain't he?

33:37.993 --> 33:41.094
All the money in a bag.
What are you lookin' at, grandpa?

33:41.094 --> 33:43.794
Pardon me, George, you got a
plan for getting outta here?

33:43.894 --> 33:45.495
Sure, boys.

33:45.695 --> 33:47.795
Here's my plan. Ha ha ha ha!

33:47.995 --> 33:50.596
They ain't never seen
ordnance like this!

33:50.696 --> 33:52.496
Thank you, folks.

33:52.796 --> 33:57.798
And remember, Jesus saves,
but George Nelson withdraws!

33:57.798 --> 33:59.698
Go fix the auto voiture, Pete.

33:59.898 --> 34:02.899
That's Babyface Nelson.

34:02.999 --> 34:05.899
Who said that?

34:06.099 --> 34:09.900
What ignorant, low-down, slanderisin'

34:10.000 --> 34:13.201
son of a bitch said that?!

34:13.301 --> 34:17.802
My name is George Nelson, get me?!

34:17.902 --> 34:21.103
She didn't mean nothin' by it, George.

34:21.203 --> 34:24.304
George Nelson! Not Babyface!

34:24.404 --> 34:28.504
You remember!
And you tell your friends!

34:28.605 --> 34:31.005
I'm George Nelson.

34:31.105 --> 34:34.406
Born to raise hell.

34:50.509 --> 34:53.710
Well, that was some fun,
now, wasn't it, George?

34:53.810 --> 34:55.011
Yeah.

34:55.110 --> 34:57.911
Almost makes me wish
I hadn'ta been saved.

34:58.111 --> 34:59.412
Jacking up banks.

34:59.512 --> 35:03.012
I can see how a fella'd derive
a whole lot of pleasure

35:03.212 --> 35:05.113
and satisfaction out of it.

35:05.213 --> 35:09.414
- It's OK.
- Hoo, dawgies!

35:12.414 --> 35:15.415
Well...

35:15.415 --> 35:19.216
I'm takin' off.

35:19.416 --> 35:27.718
You boys might as well keep my...
share of the riches.

35:27.518 --> 35:32.519
Well, where
are you going, George?

35:32.319 --> 35:35.420
I don't know. Who cares?

35:38.020 --> 35:41.021
Now, what do you suppose
is eatin' George?

35:41.121 --> 35:45.822
Well, they say that with
the thrill-seeking personality,

35:45.822 --> 35:47.522
what goes up must come down.

35:47.722 --> 35:50.923
Top of the world one minute,
haunted by megrims the next.

35:51.023 --> 35:55.624
Yes, sir, it's as if our old
friend George is a alley cat

35:55.724 --> 35:58.725
and his own damn humours
are swingin' him by the tail.

35:58.825 --> 36:02.526
I wouldn't worry, Delmar.
He'll be back on top again.

36:02.626 --> 36:08.327
I don't think we've seen
the last of George Nelson.

36:25.231 --> 36:28.332
Don't be saps for Pappy.

36:28.432 --> 36:30.732
Homer Stokes for governor.

36:30.932 --> 36:35.533
Let's sweep this state clean.
Vote for Stokes, brother.

36:35.533 --> 36:39.134
{y:i} ...meet with the darkness
{y:i} and strive

36:39.234 --> 36:44.135
{y:i} The sunny side you also may view

36:44.035 --> 36:46.536
{y:i} Keep on the sunny side

36:46.636 --> 36:48.536
{y:i} Always on the sunny side

36:48.736 --> 36:51.937
Aw, shh shh. Hang on!
I'm gonna slap one on here.

36:52.137 --> 36:54.438
Folks, here's my cousin Ezra's niece,

36:54.638 --> 36:56.438
Eudora from out of Greenwood,

36:56.638 --> 36:59.739
doin' a little number
with her cousin Tom-Tom,

36:59.839 --> 37:04.740
which I predict you
gonna enjoy thoroughly.

37:06.940 --> 37:11.241
Now, what can I do you for,
Mr. French?

37:11.341 --> 37:14.542
How can I lay a hold
of them Soggy Bottom Boys?

37:14.542 --> 37:18.043
Soggy Bottom.
I don't precisely recollect them.

37:18.143 --> 37:21.644
They cut a record a few days ago,
an old-timey harmony thing,

37:21.744 --> 37:23.744
with a guitar accomp... accomp...

37:23.944 --> 37:27.045
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah,
I remember them.

37:27.145 --> 37:28.945
Coloured fellas, I believe.

37:29.145 --> 37:31.646
Yes, sir, they a fine bunch of boys.

37:31.746 --> 37:35.147
They sang into yonder can, then skedaddled.

37:35.247 --> 37:38.948
Well, that record is just
goin' through the goddam roof.

37:39.048 --> 37:41.448
- They playin' it far away as Mobile.
- No.

37:41.548 --> 37:43.549
Whole damn state's goin' apey.

37:43.649 --> 37:46.949
Well, it was a powerful air.

