Hell I ain't. What's this Wharvey gals?
Your name's  McGills.

58:12.927 --> 58:15.228
No, sir, not since you
got hit by that train.

58:15.428 --> 58:16.928
What are you talkin' about?
I wasn't hit by a train.

58:17.128 --> 58:21.029
- Mama says you was hit by a train.
- Blooey! Nothin' left.

58:21.129 --> 58:22.830
Just a grease spot on the L & N.

58:23.030 --> 58:25.630
Damn it, I wasn't hit by any train!

58:25.730 --> 58:27.331
That's right, Mama's got
us back to Wharvey.

58:27.531 --> 58:30.631
- That's her maiden name.
- You got a maiden name, Daddy?

58:30.631 --> 58:32.732
No, Daddy don't have a maiden name...

58:32.932 --> 58:34.132
That's your misfortune.

58:34.332 --> 58:37.933
- That's right. And now mama's got a new beau.
- He's a suitor.

58:38.033 --> 58:39.734
Yeah, I heard about that.

58:39.834 --> 58:42.934
Mama says he's bona fide.

58:43.134 --> 58:45.635
Mmm. He give her a ring?

58:45.735 --> 58:47.035
Yes, sir. A big 'un.

58:47.135 --> 58:49.636
- Gold and gems.
- Mama checked it.

58:49.836 --> 58:51.736
- It's bona fide.
- He's a suitor.

58:51.936 --> 58:54.337
- What's his name?
- Vernon T Waldrip.

58:54.437 --> 58:56.237
- Uncle Vernon.
- Till tomorrow.

58:56.337 --> 58:57.638
Then he's gonna be Daddy.

58:57.938 --> 59:01.739
I am the only daddy you got.
I am the damn pater familias.

59:01.739 --> 59:05.239
But you ain't bona fide.

59:06.940 --> 59:08.440
Where's your mama?

59:08.540 --> 59:12.941
- At the Five-and-dime.
- Buying nipples.

59:13.441 --> 59:15.942
{y:i} This way

59:16.042 --> 59:20.143
{y:i} To take me home

59:20.243 --> 59:24.844
{y:i} Kiss me more...

59:27.644 --> 59:31.445
- Daddy!
- Hello, sugar! Ha ha!

59:31.545 --> 59:33.246
How's my little girl?

59:33.446 --> 59:34.946
Hi.

59:35.246 --> 59:37.747
- Who the hell's that?
- Starla Wharvey.

59:37.847 --> 59:39.747
Starla McGill, you mean.

59:39.847 --> 59:42.748
- How come you never told me about her?
- Cos you was hit by a train.

59:42.748 --> 59:45.248
That's another thing. Why are you
telling our gals I was hit by a train?

59:45.448 --> 59:47.949
Lots of respectable people
have been hit by trains.

59:48.149 --> 59:49.949
Judge Hobby, over in Cookeville,
was hit by a train.

59:50.149 --> 59:51.850
What was I supposed to tell them?

59:52.050 --> 59:54.751
That you were sent to the penal farm
and I divorced you from shame?

59:54.751 --> 59:59.252
I take your point. But it does put me in a
damn awkward position vis--vis my progeny.

59:59.252 --> 01:00:05.853
Hello, Penny.
Is this gentleman bothering you?

01:00:06.253 --> 01:00:07.553
You Waldrip?

01:00:07.854 --> 01:00:11.054
Uh-huh. That's right.

01:00:11.054 --> 01:00:14.255
Hmm.

01:00:22.957 --> 01:00:25.157
You been using my hair treatment?

01:00:25.257 --> 01:00:27.358
Your hair treatment?

01:00:27.458 --> 01:00:30.859
Excuse me.

01:00:32.359 --> 01:00:36.460
I got news  for you. In case you hadn't
noticed, I wasn't hit by a train,

01:00:36.560 --> 01:00:38.961
and I have travelled many a weary mile

01:00:39.061 --> 01:00:43.362
to be back with my wife
and my six daughters.

01:00:43.562 --> 01:00:46.762
- Seven, Daddy!
- That ain't your daddy, Alvanelle.

01:00:46.762 --> 01:00:48.163
Your daddy was hit by a train.

01:00:48.363 --> 01:00:49.763
Penny, you stop that!

01:00:49.963 --> 01:00:51.863
You stop it! Vernon here's got a job.

01:00:52.064 --> 01:00:55.164
Vernon's got prospects.
He's bona fide. What are you?

01:00:55.364 --> 01:00:56.865
I'll tell you what I am...

01:00:57.065 --> 01:01:00.265
I'm the pater familias,
and you can't marry him!

01:01:00.265 --> 01:01:02.266
I can, I am and I will, tomorrow.

01:01:02.466 --> 01:01:04.766
I gotta think about the Wharvey gals.

01:01:04.866 --> 01:01:07.067
They look to me for answers.

01:01:07.167 --> 01:01:09.467
Vernon can buy 'em
lessons on the clarinet.

01:01:09.568 --> 01:01:13.368
The only good thing you ever did for
the gals was get hit by that train!

01:01:13.568 --> 01:01:17.669
Well, you lying, unconstant succubus.

01:01:17.769 --> 01:01:21.770
Whoa, whoa, whoa!
You can't swear at my fiance!

01:01:21.770 --> 01:01:26.671
Oh, yeah?
Well, you can't marry my wife!

01:01:47.176 --> 01:01:49.977
Who is that man?

01:01:50.077 --> 01:01:52.777
He's not my husband.

01:01:52.977 --> 01:01:58.779
Just a drifter, I guess.
Just some no-account drifter.

01:02:00.679 --> 01:02:04.680
And stay out of the Woolsworth!

01:02:08.681 --> 01:02:11.081
I'll bet she does
imitations, too.

01:02:11.281 --> 01:02:14.182
Deceitful, two-faced she-wolf.

01:02:14.382 --> 01:02:16.683
Never trust a female, Delmar.

01:02:16.783 --> 01:02:21.384
Remember that one simple precept and your
time with me won't have been ill-spent.

01:02:21.484 --> 01:02:24.484
- OK, Everett.
- "Hit by a train".

01:02:24.484 --> 01:02:27.085
Truth means nothing to a woman, Delmar.

01:02:27.185 --> 01:02:30.786
Triumph of the subjective.
You ever been with a woman?

01:02:30.886 --> 01:02:33.587
Well, I've...

01:02:33.787 --> 01:02:37.387
I got to get the family farm back
before I can start thinking about that.

01:02:37.387 --> 01:02:39.288
That's right. If then.

01:02:39.488 --> 01:02:43.489
Believe me Delmar, woman's the
most fiendish instrument of torture

01:02:43.589 --> 01:02:46.189
ever devised to be Devil the days of man.

01:02:46.289 --> 01:02:49.190
Everett, I never figured you
for a pater familias.

01:02:49.290 --> 01:02:53.691
Ohh, yes. I have spread my seed.

01:02:53.791 --> 01:02:55.291
And look what it's...

01:02:57.092 --> 01:03:02.193
God damn it. What the hell...?

01:03:57.606 --> 01:04:02.507
OK, boys.
Enjoy your picture show.

01:04:06.508 --> 01:04:10.108
{y:i} I have no money, honey

01:04:10.108 --> 01:04:12.309
{y:i} How can I change?

01:04:12.409 --> 01:04:18.010
Do... not... seek the treasure.

01:04:19.711 --> 01:04:25.912
Do not... seek the treasure.

01:04:26.012 --> 01:04:27.912
It's a bushwhack.

01:04:28.113 --> 01:04:31.013
They're fixin' an ambush.

01:04:31.113 --> 01:04:35.414
Do not seek the treasure.

01:04:38.215 --> 01:04:43.816
We... we thought you was...

01:04:43.816 --> 01:04:47.017
a toad.

01:04:49.517 --> 01:04:58.619
We... thought...
you... was... a... toad.

01:04:58.519 --> 01:05:02.620
Do not seek the treasure.

01:05:02.720 --> 01:05:07.021
Quiet there!
Watch the picture!

01:05:11.122 --> 01:05:12.623
I signed that bill.

01:05:12.923 --> 01:05:15.523
I signed a dozen agriculture bills.

01:05:15.623 --> 01:05:18.424
Everyone knows
I'm a friend of the farmer.

01:05:18.524 --> 01:05:21.325
What I gotta do,
start diddling livestock?

01:05:21.525 --> 01:05:24.725
We can't do that, Daddy.
We might offend our constituency.

01:05:24.825 --> 01:05:30.227
We ain't got a constituency!
Stokes got a constituency!

01:05:30.027 --> 01:05:32.227
Well, it's a well-run campaign.

01:05:32.327 --> 01:05:34.228
Midget and broom and whatnot.

01:05:34.428 --> 01:05:37.328
- Devil his due.
- Hell of an organisation.

01:05:37.428 --> 01:05:40.629
- Say, I got an idea.
- What's that, Junior?

01:05:40.729 --> 01:05:44.430
We can hire us a little fella
even smaller than Stokes's.

01:05:44.430 --> 01:05:46.630
You slump-shouldered sack of nuts!

01:05:46.730 --> 01:05:49.631
Why, we'd look like a bunch
of johnny-come-latelys.

01:05:49.831 --> 01:05:51.832
Bringin' out our own midget.

01:05:51.932 --> 01:05:53.532
Don't matter how stumpy!

01:05:53.632 --> 01:05:58.433
And that's the goddam problem, right there.
people think Stokes has got fresh ideas.

01:05:58.433 --> 01:06:00.533
He's au courant and we're the past!

01:06:00.734 --> 01:06:02.034
It's a problem of...

01:06:02.334 --> 01:06:03.834
- Perception.
- That's right.

01:06:04.034 --> 01:06:06.935
- He's pulling our pants down.
- Gonna paddle some behind.

01:06:07.035 --> 01:06:09.235
Ain't gonna paddle it.
Gonna kick it. Real hard.

01:06:09.435 --> 01:06:13.036
- No, I believe he's gonna paddle it.
- I don't believe that's a proper description.

01:06:13.036 --> 01:06:19.038
- Well, that's how I'd characterise it.
- I believe it's more of a kickin' situation.

01:06:32.941 --> 01:06:38.442
God... God forgive me.

01:06:38.342 --> 01:06:42.643
I could not gaze upon that fireshow.

01:06:42.643 --> 01:06:45.644
- Pete.

01:06:45.844 --> 01:06:50.345
- Hold still!
- Can't... stand much longer.

01:06:50.445 --> 01:06:53.345
It was... it was
a mo-moment of weakness.

01:06:53.545 --> 01:06:55.446
Quit babblin', we gotta skedaddle.

01:06:55.646 --> 01:06:57.646
That's all I got.

01:06:57.846 --> 01:06:59.447
They lured me out for a bathe

01:06:59.547 --> 01:07:03.048
and then they dunked me,
and trussed me up like a hog,

01:07:03.248 --> 01:07:04.948
and turned me in for the bounty.

01:07:05.048 --> 01:07:07.749
Shoulda guessed it.
Typical womanly behaviour.

01:07:07.849 --> 01:07:10.349
Just lucky we left before
they came back for us.

01:07:10.449 --> 01:07:12.250
We didn't abandon you, Pete.

01:07:12.350 --> 01:07:14.550
We just thought you was a toad.

01:07:14.650 --> 01:07:17.051
No, they never did turn me into a toad.

01:07:17.151 --> 01:07:19.951
Well, that was our mistake, then.

01:07:20.052 --> 01:07:24.953
And we was beat up by a Bible salesman
and banished from Woolworths.

01:07:24.953 --> 01:07:27.953
I don't know, Everett, was it
the one branch or all of them?

01:07:28.153 --> 01:07:30.854
Well, I ain't had it easy, either, boys.

01:07:31.054 --> 01:07:35.755
Frankly, uh, well, I...

01:07:36.355 --> 01:07:38.856
I spilt my guts about the treasure.

01:07:39.056 --> 01:07:41.656
Huh?

01:07:41.856 --> 01:07:46.057
I'm awful sorry I betrayed you, fellas.

01:07:46.057 --> 01:07:49.658
Must be my Hogwallop blood.

01:07:50.458 --> 01:07:52.259
That's all right, Pete.

01:07:52.459 --> 01:07:55.460
Awful white of you to take it
like that, Everett.

01:07:55.560 --> 01:07:58.060
I feel wretched.

01:07:58.260 --> 01:08:01.761
Spoiling your play for
a million dollar point two.

01:08:01.961 --> 01:08:04.962
You should rip out my guts.

01:08:04.962 --> 01:08:07.262
No, that's all right.

01:08:09.163 --> 01:08:13.864
You boys are true friends! Ohh!

01:08:13.664 --> 01:08:16.363
You're my beaucoup friends.

01:08:16.464 --> 01:08:20.365
Pete, I don't want you to
beat yourself up about this, eh?

01:08:20.465 --> 01:08:28.067
I can't help it, but that's a...
a wonderful thing to say.

01:08:29.466 --> 01:08:33.968
Yeah. Pete, uh...

01:08:34.468 --> 01:08:38.769
Well, fact of the matter is...

01:08:40.670 --> 01:08:42.270
Damn it...

01:08:42.470 --> 01:08:45.770
There ain't no treasure.

01:08:47.371 --> 01:08:49.671
Fact of the matter is there never was.

01:08:49.772 --> 01:08:51.572
But...

01:08:51.671 --> 01:08:57.573
So where's all the money
from the armoured car job?

01:08:57.374 --> 01:09:00.174
I never knocked over no armoured car.

01:09:00.274 --> 01:09:03.675
I was sent up for practising
law without a license.

01:09:03.774 --> 01:09:05.475
- But...
- Damn it, I had to bust out.

01:09:05.675 --> 01:09:10.977
My wife wrote me she was getting
married, I gotta stop it.

01:09:10.877 --> 01:09:13.877
I had two weeks left on my sentence.

01:09:14.077 --> 01:09:16.078
I couldn't wait two weeks.
She's getting married tomorrow.

01:09:16.278 --> 01:09:24.380
My added time for the escape,
I don't get out now till 19... 87.

01:09:24.279 --> 01:09:25.979
Now, I am sorry about that.

01:09:26.279 --> 01:09:31.581
I'll be... 84 years old.

01:09:31.481 --> 01:09:35.381
I guess they'll tack on
50 years for me, too.

01:09:35.482 --> 01:09:39.783
Boys, we was chained together.
I had to tell you something.

01:09:39.883 --> 01:09:45.084
Busting out alone was not
an option. I'm sorry.

01:09:45.184 --> 01:09:48.785
84 years old.

01:09:48.685 --> 01:09:51.986
Well, I'll only be 82.

01:09:52.185 --> 01:09:54.887
You! You ruined my life!

01:09:54.987 --> 01:09:57.687
You ruined my life!

01:09:57.787 --> 01:09:59.888
I do apologize about that, Pete.

01:09:59.988 --> 01:10:04.389
84 years old! I'm becoming Papillon!

01:10:04.389 --> 01:10:05.889
Delmar!

01:10:09.990 --> 01:10:13.791
Now, boys. Boys.

01:10:26.294 --> 01:10:33.295
{y:i} Eeny meeny meiny mo

01:10:33.295 --> 01:10:37.396
{y:i} Oh hi lo hi

