01:11:51.313 --> 01:11:52.613
Noose.

01:11:52.713 --> 01:11:55.714
{y:i} No longer prayin'...

01:11:55.914 --> 01:12:00.315
Sweet Jesus, we got to save him.

01:12:00.315 --> 01:12:03.016
{y:i} I'll fix your feet
{y:i} till you can't walk

01:12:03.116 --> 01:12:08.217
{y:i} I'll lock your jaw
{y:i} till you can't talk

01:12:08.317 --> 01:12:11.518
{y:i} I'll close your eyes
{y:i} so you can't see

01:12:11.618 --> 01:12:16.119
{y:i} - It's very dark...
- The colour guard.

01:12:16.319 --> 01:12:19.819
{y:i} Death, I come to take the soul

01:12:20.020 --> 01:12:24.621
{y:i} Leave the body and leave it cold

01:12:24.621 --> 01:12:28.121
{y:i} Oh death

01:12:28.221 --> 01:12:32.422
{y:i} Whoa death

01:12:32.522 --> 01:12:38.224
{y:i} Won't you spare me over
{y:i} till another year?

01:12:39.724 --> 01:12:42.425
Brothers!

01:12:42.625 --> 01:12:45.225
Oh, brothers!

01:12:45.425 --> 01:12:53.227
We have all gathered here to preserve
our hallowed culture and heritage

01:12:53.127 --> 01:12:59.028
from intrusion,
inclusion and dilution

01:12:59.128 --> 01:13:01.929
of colour, of creed,

01:13:02.129 --> 01:13:04.130
and of our old-time religion.

01:13:04.230 --> 01:13:08.731
We aim to pull evil up by the root

01:13:08.831 --> 01:13:14.832
before it chokes out the flower
of our culture and heritage.

01:13:14.732 --> 01:13:18.533
And our women, let's not
forget those ladies, y'all,

01:13:18.633 --> 01:13:21.433
looking to us for protection

01:13:21.633 --> 01:13:26.435
from Darkies, from Jews, from Papists,

01:13:26.435 --> 01:13:29.135
and from all those smart-ass folks

01:13:29.235 --> 01:13:32.136
say we come descended from monkeys.

01:13:32.236 --> 01:13:35.437
- That's not my culture and heritage.
- Yes!

01:13:35.437 --> 01:13:36.837
Is that your culture and heritage?

01:13:37.137 --> 01:13:39.237
No!

01:13:39.438 --> 01:13:41.938
And so...

01:13:42.138 --> 01:13:44.039
we gonna hang us a Negro.

01:13:44.139 --> 01:13:47.939
Hooray!

01:13:57.242 --> 01:14:02.343
I ain't never harmed you,
neither of you gentlemen.

01:14:02.943 --> 01:14:06.944
Uh...

01:14:19.247 --> 01:14:23.347
Mm-hmm.

01:14:23.247 --> 01:14:27.148
I ain't never harmed nobody.

01:14:28.649 --> 01:14:30.949
- Hey, hey, Tommy.
- Huh?

01:14:31.049 --> 01:14:32.850
Tommy, we come to rescue you.

01:14:32.950 --> 01:14:35.050
That's mighty kind of you boys,

01:14:35.250 --> 01:14:38.451
but I don't think nothing's
going to save me now.

01:14:38.451 --> 01:14:42.352
The Devil's come
to collect his due.

01:14:42.552 --> 01:14:44.452
Don't be crazy, Tommy.

01:14:44.552 --> 01:14:46.353
You don't wanna get hanged.

01:14:46.453 --> 01:14:48.553
Well, naw, I don't reckon I do,

01:14:48.753 --> 01:14:52.854
but that's the way it seems
to be workin' out.

01:14:54.054 --> 01:14:55.755
Listen, Tommy, I got a plan.

01:14:58.555 --> 01:15:01.056
No!

01:15:05.057 --> 01:15:06.857
The colour guard is coloured.

01:15:08.858 --> 01:15:12.359
Who made them the colour guard?

01:15:13.659 --> 01:15:15.959
Run, boys!

01:15:20.660 --> 01:15:22.161
Whoa!

01:15:22.361 --> 01:15:23.461
No, no, son!

01:15:26.262 --> 01:15:30.963
Can't let that flag
touch the ground!

01:15:53.468 --> 01:15:55.468
Get your hand off me.
I can do this myself.

01:15:55.668 --> 01:15:58.169
Get away from here. I didn't
tell you to sit over here.

01:15:58.169 --> 01:16:00.069
I'm saying we should hire this man away.

01:16:00.369 --> 01:16:02.670
- That's a good idea, Pappy.
- Hell of an idea.

01:16:02.770 --> 01:16:03.670
Can't beat 'em, join 'em.

01:16:03.770 --> 01:16:06.471
Have him join us, run our campaign,
instead of that egghead's.

01:16:06.571 --> 01:16:10.672
- Enticements of power, wealth, et cetera.
- No one says no to Pappy O'Daniel.

01:16:10.672 --> 01:16:14.373
- Oh, gracious, no, not with his blandishments.
- And powers of persuasion.

01:16:14.573 --> 01:16:17.573
- What's his name again?
- The campaign manager?

01:16:17.673 --> 01:16:19.374
- Waldrip.
- Vernon Waldrip.

01:16:19.574 --> 01:16:23.075
- Vernon T Waldrip.
- Hmm.

01:16:27.876 --> 01:16:30.076
It's an invitation-only affair.

01:16:30.176 --> 01:16:32.077
We'll have to sneak in at
the service entrance.

01:16:32.277 --> 01:16:34.677
Hold on. Wait a minute.

01:16:34.777 --> 01:16:37.078
Who elected you leader of this outfit?

01:16:37.278 --> 01:16:41.379
Since we've been following your lead,
we got nothing but trouble.

01:16:41.379 --> 01:16:44.179
I've gotten this close to being strung up

01:16:44.279 --> 01:16:47.380
and consumed in a fire and whipped no end

01:16:47.380 --> 01:16:49.181
and sunstroked and soggied.

01:16:49.381 --> 01:16:50.781
And turned into a frog.

01:16:50.981 --> 01:16:52.481
He wasn't turned into a frog.

01:16:52.581 --> 01:16:56.882
Almost loved up, though.

01:16:56.882 --> 01:16:59.883
So, you're against me now, too?

01:17:00.083 --> 01:17:03.684
Is that how it is, boys?

01:17:04.184 --> 01:17:10.785
The whole world and God Almighty...
and now you?

01:17:13.386 --> 01:17:15.286
I guess I deserve it.

01:17:15.487 --> 01:17:19.087
Boys...

01:17:19.187 --> 01:17:22.088
I know that I made some
tactical mistakes,

01:17:22.288 --> 01:17:25.389
but if you just stick with me,
I got a plan.

01:17:25.389 --> 01:17:27.689
Believe me, boys, we
can fix this thing.

01:17:27.889 --> 01:17:30.390
And I'll get my wife back,
and we can get out of here.

01:17:34.291 --> 01:17:37.191
Goddam disgrace!

01:17:37.191 --> 01:17:39.792
Made a travesty of the entire evening.

01:17:39.892 --> 01:17:43.693
Ohh! What I wouldn't give
to get a hold of those agitators.

01:17:43.793 --> 01:17:47.494
I mean, whoever heard of such behaviour,
even amongst the coloured?

01:17:47.694 --> 01:17:52.295
Mulattos, maybe. I suspect some miscegenation
in their heritage. How else you gonna explain it?

01:17:52.295 --> 01:17:54.995
Using a Confederate flag as a missile!

01:17:55.196 --> 01:17:58.496
Crazy! No one's ever gonna
believe we're a real band.

01:17:58.496 --> 01:18:01.397
This gonna work. I just gotta get
close enough to talk to her.

01:18:01.497 --> 01:18:04.998
Coming with us has more future
than marrying a guy named Waldrip.

01:18:04.998 --> 01:18:07.498
I'm goddam bona fide.
I got the answers.

01:18:07.698 --> 01:18:10.899
Everett, my beard itches.

01:18:15.100 --> 01:18:18.701
Hey, hey!

01:18:21.501 --> 01:18:26.002
"In the Jailhouse Now", fellas.
Neighbourhood of B.

01:18:31.604 --> 01:18:33.604
Psst!

01:18:33.704 --> 01:18:37.705
Penny. Ahem.

01:18:38.005 --> 01:18:42.806
- It's me.
- No.

01:18:42.706 --> 01:18:44.107
Honey!

01:18:44.307 --> 01:18:48.007
{y:i} I had a friend named Ramblin' Bob

01:18:48.007 --> 01:18:50.708
{y:i} He used to steal, gamble and rob

01:18:50.908 --> 01:18:56.009
{y:i} He thought he was
{y:i} the smartest guy around

01:18:56.109 --> 01:18:57.410
{y:i} Well, I...

01:18:57.610 --> 01:19:02.311
We're leaving the state, pursuing
opportunities in another venue.

01:19:02.311 --> 01:19:04.411
I've got big plans.

01:19:04.611 --> 01:19:07.312
Not minstrelsy. This here's just a dodge.
I'm going to be a dentist.

01:19:07.412 --> 01:19:12.113
I know this guy who'll
print me up a license.

01:19:12.113 --> 01:19:15.214
{y:i} He's in the jailhouse now

01:19:15.314 --> 01:19:18.814
{y:i} Well, I told him once or twice

01:19:19.015 --> 01:19:23.115
{y:i} To stop playin' cards
{y:i} and a-shootin' dice

01:19:23.115 --> 01:19:26.716
{y:i} He's in the jailhouse now

01:19:26.816 --> 01:19:29.117
{y:i} Ah hee yodel-lay-hee-hoo

01:19:29.117 --> 01:19:32.718
{y:i} Yo heeeeee

01:19:33.018 --> 01:19:34.918
{y:i} Ah dee yodel-lay-hee

01:19:35.018 --> 01:19:38.819
{y:i} Oh de-lo tee

01:19:38.819 --> 01:19:41.820
{y:i} Yodel-lay-hee hee,
{y:i} yodel-lay-hee hee

01:19:41.920 --> 01:19:45.821
{y:i} Yodel-lay-heeeee

01:19:46.121 --> 01:19:48.121
{y:i} Bob liked to play his poker...

01:19:50.222 --> 01:19:52.522
Why, that is an improper suggestion.

01:19:52.622 --> 01:19:57.723
I-I-I can't switch sides
in the middle of a campaign...

01:19:57.623 --> 01:20:01.124
especially to work for a man
who lacks moral fibre.

01:20:01.224 --> 01:20:04.525
Moral fibre?
Why, you pasty-face son'bitch.

01:20:04.625 --> 01:20:06.225
I invented moral fibre.

01:20:06.425 --> 01:20:09.726
Pappy O'Daniel was displaying
rectitude and high-mindedness while

01:20:09.726 --> 01:20:12.127
that egghead you work for
was still messin' his drawers!

01:20:12.227 --> 01:20:15.027
- Psst! Honey.
- Go away.

01:20:15.127 --> 01:20:17.628
I want to be what
you want me to be, honey.

01:20:17.728 --> 01:20:20.528
I want you and the gals
to come with me.

01:20:20.729 --> 01:20:25.430
{y:i} To stop playin' cards
{y:i} and a-shootin' dice...

01:20:25.430 --> 01:20:28.830
What are you doing here, Pappy?

01:20:28.930 --> 01:20:31.031
I guess someone let on
we were giving out liquor.

01:20:31.131 --> 01:20:34.032
You'll be laughing out the other
side of your face come November.

01:20:34.232 --> 01:20:35.932
Pappy O'Daniel will be laughing then.

01:20:36.132 --> 01:20:39.733
- Not out the other side of his face, though.
- No. Just the regular side.

01:20:39.833 --> 01:20:43.834
{y:i} Yodel-lay-hee hee,
{y:i} yodel-lay-hee hee

01:20:44.034 --> 01:20:48.435
{y:i} Yodel-lay-heeeeee

01:20:53.036 --> 01:20:55.236
They're my daughters, too, Penny.

01:20:55.336 --> 01:20:56.837
Ain't you ever heard of...?

01:20:57.037 --> 01:20:59.337
{y:i} In constant sorrow

01:21:15.841 --> 01:21:19.742
{y:i} I am the man

01:21:19.742 --> 01:21:22.442
{y:i} Of constant sorrow

01:21:22.643 --> 01:21:25.043
{y:i} I've seen trouble...

01:21:25.143 --> 01:21:27.844
Hot damn! It's the Soggy Bottom Boys!

01:21:28.044 --> 01:21:32.645
{y:i} I bid farewell

01:21:32.645 --> 01:21:34.645
{y:i} To old Kentucky

01:21:34.745 --> 01:21:40.347
{y:i} The place where
{y:i} I was born and raised

01:21:40.447 --> 01:21:42.947
{y:i} The place where he

01:21:42.947 --> 01:21:47.248
{y:i} Was born and raised...

01:21:54.650 --> 01:21:58.151
Whoo!

01:22:05.752 --> 01:22:08.253
Holy moly! These boys are a hit!

01:22:08.353 --> 01:22:10.753
But, Pappy, they's integrated.

01:22:10.953 --> 01:22:13.254
Wait a minute.

01:22:13.254 --> 01:22:15.655
Well, I guess folks don't mind integration.

01:22:15.855 --> 01:22:19.956
You's miscegenated.
All you boys is miscegenated!

01:22:20.056 --> 01:22:21.256
Gimme a microphone!

01:22:21.456 --> 01:22:24.557
Gimme a microphone!
Gimme a microphone!

01:22:24.757 --> 01:22:30.058
These boys is not white.
Hell, they ain't even old-timey.

01:22:30.058 --> 01:22:32.558
I happen to know, ladies and gentlemen,

01:22:32.658 --> 01:22:35.459
that this band of miscreants
here, this very evening,

01:22:35.659 --> 01:22:41.060
interfered with a lynch mob
in the performance of its duties.

01:22:41.160 --> 01:22:42.561
It's true!

01:22:42.661 --> 01:22:45.161
See, I belong to a
certain secret society.

01:22:45.361 --> 01:22:48.362
I don't believe I gotta
mention its name, you know?

01:22:48.462 --> 01:22:50.863
Let 'em play! Go on!
I wanna hear them sing.

01:22:50.963 --> 01:22:52.363
Hmm.

01:22:52.563 --> 01:22:54.463
And these boys here,

01:22:54.563 --> 01:22:58.364
they trampled all over our
venerated observances and rituals.

01:22:58.364 --> 01:23:01.265
Now, this here music is
over, all right?

01:23:01.365 --> 01:23:02.865
And I have... No! Hey!

01:23:03.065 --> 01:23:05.566
Hey, I ain't... listen to me.

01:23:05.766 --> 01:23:07.766
Folks, listen to me. I...

01:23:07.866 --> 01:23:11.067
These boys desecrated a fiery cross.

01:23:12.167 --> 01:23:14.368
We's all havin' a good time!

01:23:14.468 --> 01:23:18.569
And they's convicts, folks,
fugitives escaped off the farm.

01:23:18.669 --> 01:23:22.470
Now, folks, these boys gotta
be remanded to the authorities.

01:23:22.570 --> 01:23:23.870
Criminals!

01:23:23.970 --> 01:23:26.371
And I have it from
the highest authority

01:23:26.471 --> 01:23:29.571
that that Negro sold
his soul to the Devil!

01:23:29.671 --> 01:23:31.272
Oh!

01:23:31.372 --> 01:23:34.472
W-W-Wait a minute, folks.
It's true!

01:23:34.672 --> 01:23:35.473
It's true!

01:23:36.673 --> 01:23:37.773
Wait a minute.

01:23:37.973 --> 01:23:41.074
Is you is, or is you
ain't my constituency?

01:23:41.274 --> 01:23:42.274
No!

01:23:42.374 --> 01:23:44.875
Is you is, or is you
ain't my constituency?

01:23:45.075 --> 01:23:47.175
No!

01:23:47.275 --> 01:23:49.876
Is you is...

01:23:50.076 --> 01:23:54.377
Is you is, or is you
ain't my constituency?

01:23:54.477 --> 01:23:56.878
Oh, come on, folks.

01:23:57.078 --> 01:23:58.578
No. It's Homer now.

01:23:58.778 --> 01:24:00.878
I'm a friend of the little man.

01:24:11.681 --> 01:24:14.882
This is not fair!
Hey! Come on!

01:24:17.882 --> 01:24:23.484
Come on, we got a little
misunderstanding here. God damn!

01:24:27.785 --> 01:24:32.186
{y:i} It's fair to tell

01:24:32.186 --> 01:24:34.786
{y:i} My only lover

01:24:34.886 --> 01:24:37.287
{y:i} I never expect

01:24:37.487 --> 01:24:41.088
{y:i} To see you again

01:24:41.288 --> 01:24:45.489
{y:i} For I'm bound to ride

01:24:45.689 --> 01:24:48.389
{y:i} That northern railroad

01:24:48.389 --> 01:24:53.290
{y:i} Perhaps I'll die upon that train

01:24:53.390 --> 01:24:58.992
{y:i} Perhaps he'll die
{y:i} upon his train...

01:24:58.992 --> 01:25:02.392
God damn! Opportunity knocks!

01:25:02.492 --> 01:25:04.793
Get out of my way!

01:25:04.993 --> 01:25:07.494
{y:i} I'm just a stranger

01:25:07.594 --> 01:25:10.194
{y:i} In case you ever

01:25:10.394 --> 01:25:12.595
{y:i} See your man...

01:25:13.895 --> 01:25:18.596
{y:i} But there is one promise

01:25:18.596 --> 01:25:20.797
{y:i} That is given

01:25:20.997 --> 01:25:23.397
{y:i} I'll meet you on

01:25:23.597 --> 01:25:26.198
{y:i} God's golden shore

01:25:26.398 --> 01:25:29.098
{y:i} He'll meet you on

01:25:29.198 --> 01:25:31.799
{y:i} God's golden shore

01:25:31.899 --> 01:25:35.800
That's fine. That's fine!

01:25:38.301 --> 01:25:40.801
Ladies and gentlemans,

01:25:40.901 --> 01:25:43.302
here and listening at home,

01:25:43.402 --> 01:25:46.502
the great state of Mississippi...

01:25:46.602 --> 01:25:48.503
Pappy O'Daniel, Governor...

01:25:48.703 --> 01:25:54.604
wants to thank the Soggy Bottom Boys
for that wonderful performance.

01:25:56.705 --> 01:26:00.506
And it looks like the only man
in this great state

01:26:00.606 --> 01:26:02.506
who ain't a music lover

01:26:02.706 --> 01:26:06.307
is my esteemed opponent
in the upcoming, Homer Stokes.

01:26:06.407 --> 01:26:08.907
There ain't no accounting for taste.

01:26:10.308 --> 01:26:13.408
Sounded to me like he was harbouring
some kind of hateful grudge

01:26:13.508 --> 01:26:15.309
against the Soggy Bottom Boys

01:26:15.409 --> 01:26:17.909
on account of their
rough and rowdy past.

01:26:19.910 --> 01:26:22.911
Looks like Homer Stokes
is the kind of fellow

01:26:23.011 --> 01:26:25.311
who wants to cast the first stone.

01:26:25.411 --> 01:26:28.112
Well, I'm with you, folks.

01:26:28.312 --> 01:26:31.413
I'm a forgive-and-forget
Christian, and I say...

01:26:31.513 --> 01:26:37.114
if their rambunctiousness and
misdemeanoring is behind them...

01:26:37.114 --> 01:26:38.214
It is, ain't it?

01:26:38.314 --> 01:26:40.015
Yes, sir, it is.

01:26:40.215 --> 01:26:42.215
Well, then, I say,

01:26:42.315 --> 01:26:44.716
by the power vested in me,

01:26:44.816 --> 01:26:49.217
these boys is hereby pardoned!

01:26:51.617 --> 01:26:54.018
And furthermore...

01:26:54.218 --> 01:26:56.918
in the second Pappy
O'Daniel administration,

01:26:57.018 --> 01:27:00.319
these boys is gonna be my brain trust!

01:27:04.420 --> 01:27:06.220
What's that mean, Everett?

01:27:06.420 --> 01:27:10.421
Well Delmar, it means you and me
and Pete and Tommy are gonna be

01:27:10.621 --> 01:27:12.822
the power behind the
throne, so to speak.

01:27:13.022 --> 01:27:15.623
Oh, OK.

01:27:15.723 --> 01:27:20.424
So, without further ado, and
by way of endorsing my candidacy,

01:27:20.424 --> 01:27:21.924
the Soggy Bottom Boys

01:27:22.124 --> 01:27:26.325
is gonna lead us all in a
chorus of "You Are My Sunshine".

01:27:27.425 --> 01:27:30.126
Ain't you, boys?

01:27:30.026 --> 01:27:31.226
One of our favourites.

01:27:31.526 --> 01:27:36.327
Son... you're gonna go far.

01:27:36.127 --> 01:27:38.628
{y:i} You are my sunshine

01:27:38.728 --> 01:27:41.028
{y:i} My only sunshine

01:27:41.228 --> 01:27:43.729
{y:i} You make me happy

01:27:43.829 --> 01:27:46.129
{y:i} When skies are grey

01:27:46.230 --> 01:27:48.730
{y:i} You'll never know, dear

01:27:48.830 --> 01:27:51.531
{y:i} How much I love you

01:27:51.731 --> 01:27:53.131
{y:i} Please don't take

01:27:53.331 --> 01:27:57.932
{y:i} My sunshine away

01:28:00.133 --> 01:28:03.733
I guess Vernon T Waldrip
is gonna be going on relief.

01:28:03.733 --> 01:28:06.634
Maybe I can throw a
little patronage his way,

01:28:06.734 --> 01:28:09.735
get him a job digging ditches
or rounding up stray dogs.

01:28:09.735 --> 01:28:12.235
So, is the marriage off, Miss Wharvey?

01:28:12.435 --> 01:28:16.036
McGill. No. The marriage
will take place as planned.

01:28:16.136 --> 01:28:17.437
With little change of cast.

01:28:17.537 --> 01:28:20.237
Me and the little lady are
gonna pick up the pieces

01:28:20.437 --> 01:28:23.638
and re-tie the knot,
mixaphorically speaking.

01:28:23.738 --> 01:28:25.838
You boys are invited, of course.

01:28:26.039 --> 01:28:27.739
Hell, you're the best men.

01:28:27.939 --> 01:28:30.139
I already got the rings.

01:28:30.340 --> 01:28:33.940
- Where's your ring, honey?
- I ain't worn it since our divorce came true.

01:28:34.040 --> 01:28:37.141
Must still be in the roll-top in the
old cabin. Never thought I'd need it.

01:28:37.241 --> 01:28:39.542
Vernon bought one, encrusted with jewels.

01:28:39.742 --> 01:28:42.942
Now's the time to buy it off him cheap.

01:28:42.942 --> 01:28:46.643
We ain't getting married with
his ring. You said you'd changed.

01:28:46.843 --> 01:28:49.244
- Yours is just an old pewter thing.
- There ain't gonna be no weddin'.

01:28:49.444 --> 01:28:51.944
- It's just a symbol, honey.
- No wedding.

01:28:51.944 --> 01:28:53.345
We'll go fetch it with ya, Everett.

01:28:53.645 --> 01:28:56.445
It's just... Shut up, Delmar.
It's just a symbol.

01:28:56.545 --> 01:29:00.046
I've spoken my piece and counted to three.

01:29:00.146 --> 01:29:03.947
She counted to three. God damn it.

01:29:04.047 --> 01:29:06.948
She counted to three. Son of a bitch!

01:29:07.048 --> 01:29:09.548
You have any idea how far that cabin is?

01:29:25.652 --> 01:29:26.952
George?

01:29:27.052 --> 01:29:28.753
Hello, boys!

01:29:28.953 --> 01:29:33.154
Well, these little men finally caught
up with the criminal of the century.

01:29:33.154 --> 01:29:35.354
Looks like the chair for George Nelson!

01:29:35.454 --> 01:29:41.956
Yup, gonna electrify me. I'm gonna
go off like a roman candle!

01:29:41.956 --> 01:29:45.357
20,000 volts chasing a rabbit
through yours truly!

01:29:45.557 --> 01:29:49.257
Goddamn, I'm gonna suck all
the power right out of the state!

01:29:49.357 --> 01:29:53.958
Gonna shoot sparks out of my head
and lightning from my fingertips!

01:29:53.958 --> 01:29:58.359
I'm George Nelson, and I'm
feeling ten feet tall!

01:29:58.359 --> 01:30:03.161
Looks like George is
right back on top again.

01:30:03.261 --> 01:30:04.461
Cow killer!

01:30:17.064 --> 01:30:20.765
Well, at least you boys get
to see the ancestral manse,

01:30:20.965 --> 01:30:25.466
the home where I spent so many
happy day in the bosom of my family.

01:30:25.566 --> 01:30:28.866
Refugin', if you will, with
a mighty oak tree out front

01:30:28.866 --> 01:30:33.367
and a happy little tyre swing on it.

01:30:36.468 --> 01:30:41.569
Where's the happy little tyre swing?

01:30:41.769 --> 01:30:44.870
End of the road, boys.

01:30:44.970 --> 01:30:47.071
- No. Wait a minute.
- Let's go, boys.

01:30:47.171 --> 01:30:51.672
It's had its twists and turns,
now it deposits you here.

01:30:51.772 --> 01:30:52.872
Wait a minute.

01:30:53.072 --> 01:30:58.573
You have eluded fate and you have
eluded me for the last time.

01:30:58.473 --> 01:31:01.574
- Tie their hands, boys.
- You can't do this, now.

01:31:01.674 --> 01:31:04.474
Didn't know you'd be bringing a friend.

01:31:04.574 --> 01:31:08.675
He'll just have to wait his turn,
share one of your graves.

01:31:08.675 --> 01:31:12.176
You can't do it, we just got
pardoned by the Governor himself!

01:31:12.276 --> 01:31:16.377
- It went out on the radio.
- Is that right?

01:31:19.078 --> 01:31:22.979
Well, we ain't got a radio.

01:31:23.979 --> 01:31:27.780
God have mercy.

01:31:30.680 --> 01:31:33.381
{y:i} You

01:31:33.481 --> 01:31:35.181
{y:i} Got to go

01:31:35.381 --> 01:31:38.182
{y:i} To that lonesome valley

01:31:38.282 --> 01:31:42.083
{y:i} You

01:31:42.183 --> 01:31:48.284
{y:i} Whoa, got...

01:31:48.184 --> 01:31:49.785
It ain't fittin'.

01:31:49.985 --> 01:31:51.285
It ain't the law.

01:31:51.385 --> 01:31:54.686
- The law?
{y:i} To go...

01:31:54.786 --> 01:31:57.887
The law is a human institution.

01:31:57.987 --> 01:32:01.487
{y:i} Nobody else

01:32:01.687 --> 01:32:04.488
{y:i} Can go there for you, no...

01:32:04.588 --> 01:32:07.489
Perhaps you should start
making your prayers.

01:32:07.589 --> 01:32:12.390
{y:i} Whoa

01:32:12.390 --> 01:32:18.891
{y:i} Got

01:32:18.791 --> 01:32:20.492
{y:i} To go...

01:32:20.592 --> 01:32:24.993
Oh, my God. Everett?

01:32:25.193 --> 01:32:28.594
Tommy, I'm sorry we got you into this.

01:32:28.694 --> 01:32:32.394
Good Lord... What do we do?

01:32:32.494 --> 01:32:38.496
{y:i} By yourself

01:32:38.596 --> 01:32:41.797
{y:i} Whoa...

01:32:41.897 --> 01:32:44.797
Oh, Lord...

01:32:44.897 --> 01:32:49.798
Please look down and
recognise us poor sinners.

01:32:51.099 --> 01:32:53.099
Please, Lord.

01:32:53.399 --> 01:32:57.200
I just want to see my daughters again.

01:32:57.300 --> 01:33:01.201
I've been separated
from my family for so long.

01:33:01.201 --> 01:33:04.602
I know I've been guilty of
pride and sharp dealing.

01:33:04.702 --> 01:33:06.902
I'm sorry that I turned my back on you,

01:33:07.102 --> 01:33:10.003
forgive me.

01:33:10.003 --> 01:33:12.904
We're helpless, Lord.

01:33:13.004 --> 01:33:16.504
For the sake of my family,
for Tommy's sake.

01:33:16.704 --> 01:33:20.405
For Delmar's and Pete's.

01:33:21.406 --> 01:33:25.406
Let me see my daughters again, Lord.

01:33:25.706 --> 01:33:30.708
Help us, please.

01:33:43.611 --> 01:33:47.811
{y:i} You got to go

01:33:47.811 --> 01:33:50.812
{y:i} To the lonesome valley

01:33:50.912 --> 01:34:00.214
{y:i} Yes, sir, you, whoa

01:34:00.014 --> 01:34:05.415
{y:i} Got

